tables.table_schema:
CREATE TABLE influencers (
    influencer_id UUID PRIMARY KEY,
    influencer_name VARCHAR(50) NOT NULL,
    influencer_email VARCHAR(100) UNIQUE,
    followers_count INT,
    engagement_rate FLOAT
)

CREATE TABLE Collaborations (
  id INT PRIMARY KEY,
  influencer_id INT,
  brand_name VARCHAR(50),
  partnership_type VARCHAR(50),
  collaboration_date DATE,
  FOREIGN KEY (influencer_id) REFERENCES Influencers(id)
);

CREATE TABLE collaborations (
    collaboration_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    collaboration_name VARCHAR,
    collaboration_type VARCHAR,
    collaborator_id INT,
    collaboration_date DATE
);

CREATE TABLE partnerships (
    partnership_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    partnership_name VARCHAR,
    partnership_type VARCHAR,
    partner_id INT,
    start_date DATE,
    end_date DATE
);

CREATE TABLE collaborations (
  collaboration_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
  partner_id INT,
  influencer_id INT,
  collaboration_date DATE,
  collaboration_description TEXT
);

CREATE TABLE Influencers (
    influencer_id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,
    name VARCHAR(50),
    followers INT,
    category VARCHAR(50),
    engagement_rate FLOAT
);

CREATE TABLE Brands (
    brand_id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,
    name VARCHAR(50),
    industry VARCHAR(50),
    website VARCHAR(100),
    contact_person VARCHAR(50)
);

CREATE TABLE Collaborations (
    collaboration_id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,
    influencer_id INT,
    brand_id INT,
    start_date DATE,
    end_date DATE,
    payment FLOAT
);

CREATE TABLE Campaigns (
    campaign_id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,
    brand_id INT,
    campaign_name VARCHAR(100),
    start_date DATE,
    end_date DATE,
    budget FLOAT
);

CREATE TABLE Interactions (
    interaction_id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,
    collaboration_id INT,
    interaction_type VARCHAR(50),
    interaction_date DATE,
    comments TEXT
);
